+Name:           nodejs-chalk
+Version:        5.3.0
+Release:        0
+Summary:        Terminal string styling done right
+License:        MIT
+URL:            https://github.com/chalk/chalk
+Source:         https://registry.npmjs.org/chalk/-/chalk-%{version}.tgz
+BuildArch:      noarch
+
+%description
+Chalk is a terminal string styling solution. It provides a clean and
+consistent API for formatting text in the terminal with colors and styles.
+
+It supports 256 and truecolor (16 million color) output, chained
+styling, nested styles, automatic detection of supported color levels,
+and works consistently across different terminals and platforms.
+
+%prep
+%setup -q -n package
+
+%build
+# No build step needed for pure JavaScript
+
+%install
+mkdir -p %{buildroot}%{nodejs_default_library_dir}/chalk
+cp -a * %{buildroot}%{nodejs_default_library_dir}/chalk/
+
+%fdupes -s %{buildroot}%{nodejs_default_library_dir}/chalk
+
+%files
+%dir %{nodejs_default_library_dir}/chalk
+%{nodejs_default_library_dir}/chalk/package.json
+%{nodejs_default_library_dir}/chalk/source/
+%{nodejs_default_library_dir}/chalk/license
+%{nodejs_default_library_dir}/chalk/readme.md
+
+%changelog
